&lt;p&gt;The EBP role is one that doesn’t always neatly fit within the 9-6 day, so we’re looking for a go-getter who’s eager to be flexible and available, even outside traditional working hours. Because the role (and our exec team) is so dynamic, this person must possess strong business judgment and communication skills needed to interact with a variety of people and job functions, internally and externally. Our ideal candidate is someone who is excited to grow with our company and build a trusted, long-term partnership with our leadership team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will accomplish:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a trusted extension of the executives — anticipating shifting priorities, sequencing competing demands across two leaders, and making judgment calls on their behalf when appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate the executive&#39;s day-to-day fluently — managing complex calendaring, travel coordination across the US and abroad, expense reporting, and meeting logistics with precision and minimal oversight, making judgment calls based on known business priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the operating cadence of recurring leadership forums and All Hands — including agenda development, content coordination, pre-reads, note-taking, and tracking decisions and follow-ups through to completion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the execution of executive projects and initiatives — coordinating timelines, organizing stakeholders, tracking decisions, and ensuring follow-through across cross-functional teams, with a path to driving these end-to-end over time&

